Former Enugu Ranger Stewart, Kalu Orji who has been unattached since the start of the 2018 NPFL Season has agreed to a deal to Kano Pillars FC until the end of the season with an option to extend his stay at the Kano based club even further if both parties are willing to, National Daily learnt .

The assistant captain of the Nigeria CHAN Eagles to this year’s CAF CHAN Championship put pens to paper on Wednesday 11th April, 2018 and was subsequently unveiled to the media by the Club Chairman, Alhaji Tukur Babangida.

National Daily gathered that Orji  was at his first training sessions with the team  yesterday and would be available to play competitively in the NPFL spotting the number 6 jersey for Pillars once the mid-season transfer window opens.
